@flexiarg vsatelier/return-loop
@title Return Loop (Outcomes as New Stories)
@audience programme designers, community organisers, action researchers
@tone analytic
@style design-pattern
@sigils [🔄/返]
@references [vsatelier/decision-provenance vsatelier/annotation-as-commitment vsatlas/capacity-building-sustainability]

! conclusion:
  Outcomes of actions taken from the constellation should re-enter it as
  new stories, closing the loop between seeing, deciding, acting, and
  witnessing.

  + context: You are designing a living system where action feeds back into shared knowledge. This does not apply to one-off analyses where no follow-up is expected.
  + IF:
    A community acts on a pattern surfaced by the constellation — they
    run a programme, change a practice, allocate a resource.

  + HOWEVER:
    If the outcome of that action is never recorded as a story, the
    constellation becomes a static snapshot of the past. The community
    cannot see whether their actions changed anything.

  + THEN:
    Encourage (or structure) the creation of outcome stories: what
    happened after the decision, what changed, what surprised. These
    stories enter the constellation as new nodes. Links from the
    decision record to the outcome story close the loop visually —
    an arc from "we decided" to "this is what happened."

  + BECAUSE:
    The return loop transforms the constellation from a diagnostic
    instrument into a learning cycle. Each pass through
    see → deliberate → act → witness deepens the community's
    understanding of its own situation and its capacity to change it.

  + STATUS:
    status[sketch]

  + NEXT-STEPS:
    next[Define an "outcome story" template that prompts for before/after, surprises, and unresolved questions.]
    next[Design the visual representation: how does a return-loop arc differ from an interpretive link?]
    next[Identify one completed action from an existing pilot and retroactively model the return loop.]
